# Changelog

All notable changes to the Intermarket Divergence Scanner.

Versions prior to v8.5 used a "compare last 2 swings" approach. v8.5 introduced a fundamentally different detection algorithm. Changes within the v8.x series are cumulative.

---

## v8.7 (June 2026)

**Bug fixes identified through manual blind review of Feb 25 signals.**

### Fixed
- **Dedup by sw2 identity** — Previously deduped by 30-minute time bucket, which allowed the same SMT (identical sw1/sw2 pair) to generate multiple signals across bucket boundaries. Now deduplicates by `sw2_conf_time`, so each unique SMT fires exactly once.
- **FVG search starts from sw2 confirmation** — Previously searched for FVGs starting from the signal bar (which could be delayed by caching/bucketing). Now starts from the bar after sw2 confirmation, catching FVGs that form immediately after the structural break.

### Changed
- `ES_FVG_MIN` lowered from 1.0pt to 0.5pt — a 0.5pt FVG on Feb 25 would have been a 3R winner. Under review for potential overfit; may revert for out-of-sample testing.

