## v8.6 (June 2026)

**Multi-sw2 candidate evaluation and parallel sw1 detection.**

### Added
- **Multi-sw2 candidates** — Last 5 confirmed swings considered as potential sw2 anchors (newest first), not just the single most recent swing. This catches SMTs where the structural break happened a few swings back.
- **Parallel sw1 lookup** — sw1 on the failing instrument is now found by timestamp-matching with sw1 on the confirming instrument (within 2-minute tolerance). Previously reported "most recent prior swing" which didn't match the parallel structural comparison a discretionary trader actually makes.
- **`confirmations_count` column** — Tracks how many prior structural references sw2 broke that the other instrument failed to break. Higher counts indicate stronger divergence.
- **`alt_sw1_times` column** — Lists additional confirmed sw1 timestamps when confirmations_count > 1.
- **sw1 ≠ sw2 guard** — The failing instrument's parallel sw1 must be a different swing than its sw2 (prevents edge case where both resolve to the same point).

### Performance
- Added caching for macro bias (per 15-min bucket) and 5m SMT confluence (per 5-min bucket) to reduce computation from ~60s to ~19s per file.

