## v8.5 (June 2026)

**Complete rewrite of SMT detection logic.**

### Changed
- **Walk-back algorithm** replaces "compare last 2 swings":
  - sw2 = most recent confirmed swing on each instrument
  - Walk back through up to 20 prior swings (same day) to find sw1 that sw2 wick-broke
  - SMT exists when one instrument confirms (broke structure) and the other fails
- **Wick break** replaces body break for structural comparison — `sw2_high > sw1_high` (or inverse for lows)
- **sw2 staleness**: 120 minutes on 1m chart, 36 bars on 5m chart
- **Same-day session boundary** — sw1 must be from the same calendar date as the signal
- **Removed structural pullback check** — no longer meaningful with multi-swing lookback; staleness window handles recency

### Added
- **15m macro bias engine** (from v8.3) — 3-timeframe structural bias classification
  - Sequence analysis: HH+HL = bullish, LH+LL = bearish
  - Momentum classification: ≥80% of previous impulse leg = strong, <80% = slowing
  - Combined bias requires ES and NQ agreement
- **5m SMT confluence layer** (from v8.4) — lenient mode blocks only on opposing 5m SMT
- **`find_failing_sw1` function** — Reports the actual structural reference point on the failing instrument (not a duplicate of sw2)

---

## v8.4 (June 2026)

**5m SMT confluence layer.**

### Added
- 5m SMT confluence check — each 1m signal is evaluated against 5m structural divergence in the same lookback window
- Two modes: **strict** (requires agreeing 5m SMT) and **lenient** (only blocks on opposing 5m SMT)
- Lenient mode selected as default after strict mode reduced signals to 6 total (too aggressive)
- Output adds `smt5m_status` column: agree / oppose / conflicted / none

---

## v8.3 (June 2026)

**15m macro bias engine replaces session open midpoint filter.**

### Changed
- Replaced session open midpoint macro filter with 15m structural bias engine
- Bias classification uses swing sequence (HH+HL = bullish, LH+LL = bearish) plus momentum assessment (impulse leg comparison at 80% threshold)
- Per-signal bias evaluation — bias evolves through the session as new 15m bars close
- Combined bias requires ES and NQ directional agreement
- States: BULLISH, BULLISH (SLOWING), BEARISH, BEARISH (SLOWING), TRANSITIONAL, CONFLICTED

---

## v8.2 (June 2026)

**FVG selection and staleness improvements.**

### Changed
- FVG selection picks the **earliest valid** FVG after the SMT (not the first one found in the lookahead scan)
- sw1 staleness limit: sw1 must be within 60 minutes of sw2 on the 1m chart
- `SMT_IN_FVG` entry takes priority over `FVG_AFTER_SMT` during deduplication when both exist for the same divergence

